# blkhistd

A daemon that keeps a time stamped database of storage mappings

#### Building
required packages: make gcc systemd-devel sqlite-devel


# Install postgres and create a database block_history

https://developer.fedoraproject.org/tech/database/postgresql/about.html

Remote postgres

find / -name "postgresql.conf" - add :

listen_addresses = '*'

Add the following line to the end of /var/lib/pgsql/data/pg_hba.conf file:

host    all             all              0.0.0.0/0                       md5
host    all             all              ::/0  

service postgresql restart